Link failure with automatic rerouting to backup path.

Topology:
      2
     / \
    1   4
     \ /
      3

Tests:
1) Primary path usage before failure
2) Triggered updates on link failure
3) Automatic rerouting to backup path
4) Link recovery detection
5) Return to optimal path after recovery

Expected behavior:
- t=100: DATA uses primary path 1→2→4 (cost 20ms)
- t=150: Link (2,4) fails, triggered updates sent
- t=200: DATA uses backup path 1→3→4 (cost 50ms)
- t=300: Link (2,4) recovers, triggered updates sent
- t=350: DATA uses primary path 1→2→4 again (cost 20ms)

This test verifies resilience and dynamic rerouting capabilities.
